post_text:
JUNE 4TH -LAST DAY MEALS WILL BE PROVIDED

Healthy Meals for Frenchtown Kids 18 and Under

Frenchtown School District is partnering with the USDA in providing free healthy meals for all children during this closure, to ensure that our students grow and thrive while away from the school environment. If you are interested in receiving free breakfast and lunch each school day, simply contact your student’s building secretary or let your child(ren)’s bus driver know when they deliver distance learning materials. No application or registration is required. Meals will be available for curbside pickup at Frenchtown Elementary School from 8:00 a.m. to 11:00 a.m., and will also be delivered by bus on each route.

post_text: In Mrs. America’s counseling classes, students in K-3 went on their first secret mission of kindness. Each classroom received a kindness plant to pass along to someone in our school. The mission: to spread as much kindness around the school as possible. The students learned that the best kind of kindness is the kindness that is passed on and keeps growing. All of the plants, dirt, and cans were donated by community members, who at the time of their donation did not realize the impact of their kindness. Moving forward, plant kindness wherever you can!

post_text:
Frenchtown Developmental Screening
Thursday, October 3rd, 2019
Frenchtown Elementary School
Age Birth through 5 years
2:00 pm till 5:00 pm

Frenchtown Developmental Screening is scheduled for Thursday,
October 3rd, 2019 at the Frenchtown Elementary School for Children birth through 5 years of age residing in the Frenchtown School District. Please note this is not a preschool readiness test, but a screening for potential developmental delays. Screening is conducted in the areas of Speech/Language, Hearing, Vision, Knowledge/Reasoning, and Motor Skills. Assessment is comprehensive and usually takes 60 to 90 minutes. If you have any concerns regarding delays in any of these developmental areas, please call the Frenchtown Elementary Office at 626-2620 to schedule an appointment.

Bring your family and friends to a movie on the lawn to support two Frenchtown teachers fighting cancer, Judy Everett and Justine Luebke. Secret Life of Pets 2 will be showing, Iron Cakes will be selling yummy waffles, Kornutopia will be selling buttery popcorn, and blue beverages will be for sale! The cost is $20 for a family or $5 for an individual. The gate will open at 6:30 and the movie will start at 7:30. Bring your blankets, chairs, and favorite stuffed pet to enjoy the movie and support some great teachers!
Date: September 21,2019
Time: Gates open @ 6:30---Movie Starts@7:30
Where: Frenchtown High School

Frenchtown K-6 School added 9 new photos.
February 1, 2019 at 4:10 PM ·

On Wednesday our students attended an assembly titled: The Chain Reaction of Kindness: How one small act of kindness can change our family, classrooms, school, and community. As part of that assembly some Frenchtown students, parents, and staff members donated their hair to companies that make wigs for children who have had medically related hair loss. This was their opportunity to start a chain reaction of kindness. In the assembly students and staff were challenged to make a choice to spark a chain reaction on their own: picking up garbage, asking a friend to play, compliments, sharing, letting others play, meeting someone new, helping where you see a need, etc. There are 1000s of ways to be kind! We encourage everyone in our school community to start a chain reaction of kindness! Happy February Everyone!

post_text:
Frenchtown K-6 School Kick-off theme: CAN!!!

Our Olweaus Anti-Bullying/MBI theme for the school year is CAN! CAN stands for Character, Attitude, Never Quit! In our kick off assembly today students learned about positive, character building attributes that we can practice to make this school year amazing. WHO CAN be kind, work hard, play fair, cooperate, learn, listen, stand up against mean and show empathy? WE CAN-YOU CAN-I CAN! A special thank you to the Frenchtown Elementary PTA for sponsoring the U of M Drumline who surprised us during the assembly! Let’s make this school year amazing – we know WE CAN!

post_text:
Frenchtown 2017-18 Graduation Processional
The 2017-18 Graduation Processional was held on the South Campus. Our K-6 students were able to look up to the graduates with awe and enthusiasm as they walked the hallways of our elementary. This year’s walk was led by Karen Nelson who will be retiring from Frenchtown Schools. She has taught here for 17 years and will be sorely missed.

Students in grades K-5 held pennants and sat while the graduates filed by. Many high-fives were exchanged and the elementary students looked up in reverence toward the graduating class. Hopefully they were thinking to themselves, “This is all possible if I TRY!!” We would like to wish the graduates the very best in their endeavors and offer them this advice: All things are possible if U TRY! Good Luck Class of 2018!

2nd Graders Explore Careers
K-2 Students have been exploring careers in Counselor Education with Mrs. America. Career Pathways of Healthcare, Civil, Safety, and Education were explored. The students had a blast learning about post-secondary options after high school. Our students learned that some careers required a college education while other careers occur after training. Students also learned that in their respective classrooms they are learning and preparing for their future careers. All things are possible if U TRY!
